						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up near the temple of Basavaṇṇa.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṁghaṇa—A.D. 1221.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Vishu</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Ṣiṁgaḷa, Jyeshṭha śu. [5], Thursday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1221, May 27, Thursday.</hi> It records the death of <hi rend="bold">Mādaya-Nāyaka</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Iṭage,</hi> who died after rescuing the cows in a cattle-raid by <hi rend="bold">Malaya-Nāyaka</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Kandagale.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
